# People Registry (EXAMPLE)

> Copy to `people.md` and fill in real values. This is the canonical mapping of
> humans to identity signals and permissions. Agents read it on session start to
> identify who they're talking to and adapt (communication style, permissions,
> routing). If identity cannot be resolved, the agent asks rather than guesses.

## Operator (you)

- **Name**: <Your Name>
- **Role**: Principal / owner
- **Email**: <you@yourcompany.com>
- **Phone**: <+1...>
- **Permissions**: full
- **Comms preference**: SMS for urgent, weekly email digest otherwise

## Collaborators

| Name | Role | Email | Phone | Permissions |
|------|------|-------|-------|-------------|
| <Name> | <role> | <email> | <phone> | <scope> |

## Resolution rule

If an inbound message's sender can't be matched to a person here, do not assume —
ask who it is before acting on their behalf.
